<frontend-requirements>
- Vue.js application with TypeScript
- Node.js runtime environment
- Tailwind for CSS styling
- Prefer Tailwind tokens from the Aleph Alpha design system over hardcoding colors or styling fonts
- Always prioritize Aleph Alpha (AA) components from `@aleph-alpha/ds-components-vue` UI library over custom component generation from scratch, unless no suitable option exists
</frontend-requirements>

<components>
- Use existing list components from the design system
- Maintain TypeScript strict typing throughout
- Follow Vue.js composition API patterns
</components>

<architecture>
- components should not directly talk to the API
- usually, components -> stores -> api service -> http calls
</architecture>

<styling>
- Use Aleph Alpha design system tokens
- Avoid hardcoded colors, fonts, or spacing values
- Prefer utility-first approach with Tailwind CSS
</styling>
